    "narrative": "The crown jewel of today\u2019s lineup is undoubtedly **Corbin Carroll**, who earns an elite 87.14 efficiency score against M\u00e1rquez. This matchup is a perfect storm for our strategy: not only does he benefit from a massive 19% skill adjustment against a high xERA pitcher, but M\u00e1rquez\u2019s slow delivery\u2014allowing an 86% success rate on stolen bases\u2014makes **Corbin Carroll** the priority anchor for our pursuit of the scarcest category. Meanwhile, **Brice Turang** (63.95) and **Seiya Suzuki** (68.49) serve as vital secondary drivers. **Brice Turang** maximizes his leadoff position and favorable matchup against Keller, while **Seiya Suzuki** leverages a strong wind-out projection to bolster his power upside, despite a slight platoon penalty.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the Ghost Ride the WHIP front office was the exclusion of **Max Muncy** (50.89), who narrowly missed the starting nine. While **Max Muncy** presents a serviceable floor, the optimizer favored the higher ceiling of **Tyler Soderstrom** and the utility upside of **Josh Naylor**. Similarly, **Austin Riley** (44.19) was relegated to the bench due to the significant dampening effect of facing a high-caliber arm like Wheeler, as our model remains disciplined in avoiding sub-optimal matchups to protect our daily game caps. While we monitor the rainout status of **Mickey Moniak**, the roster remains optimized for high-efficiency run production. We are closely watching the \"Lineup Pending\" status for players like **Alex Freeland**, whose value as a nine-hole hitter is particularly volatile; however, his switch-hitting versatility and wind-aided park factors keep him just ahead of our remaining bench depth like **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Jose Caballero**.",
